_Nif’al_ Past Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_nif’al_ past tense]] follows the following conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|                | *Singular* |\<                            | *Plural* |\< |
| *First-Person* | נִכְבַּשְׁתִּי<br>_nichbashti_<br>I was conquered | \< | נִכְבַּשְׁנוּ<br>_nichbashnu_<br>We were conquered | \< |
| *Second-Person* | נִכְבַּשְׁתָּ <br>_nichbashtau_<br> You [male] were conquered | נִכְבַּשְׁתְּ <br>_nichbasht_<br> You [female] were conquered  | נִכְבַּשְׁתֶּם <br>_nichbashtem_<br> You [males] were conquered  | נִכְבַּשְׁתֶּן <br>_nichbashten_<br> You [females] were conquered  |
| *Third-Person* | נִכְבַּשׁ <br>_nichbash_<br> He was conquered | נִכְבְּשָׁה <br>_nichbeshau_<br> She was conquered  | נִכְבְּשׁוּ <br>_nichbeshu_<br> They [male or female] were conquered  | \< |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎כ, ‎ב, and ש above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
